4/5 At that point the attacker waited until most of the team went to bed, and started an attack, posting a fake mint site, that if you connected to and signed transactions would steal any valuable NFTs you have.

The affected team member has had their roles removed, pw reset.

3/5 This directed them to a phishing website.

The phishing website asked them to drag a button to their bookmarks bar. This button contains Javascript, and is known as a 'bookmarklet'.

At this point the team member went to Discord in browser, ran the bookmark to 'verify'

2/5 A team member with admin level permissions was contacted by a scammer asking for a collaboration. The team member was asked to join the Discord of the fake collaboration project (fake Garbage Friends Discord). At this point the team member clicked on a fake captcha/dyno bot
